<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,260,539]" box="[151,572,260,287]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,260,287]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
19.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,260,539]" box="[199,1294,296,323]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,296,323]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Distribution.</emphasis>
Thus far restricted to northwestern Europe. 
<collectingCountry box="[848,947,297,323]" name="Portugal" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: three northernmost provinces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,260,539]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,333,359]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Ecology.</emphasis>
Recorded from four macrohabitat categories in 
<collectingCountry box="[855,953,333,359]" name="Portugal" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, with most specimens collected near agricultural land and in a permanent pasture (Lameiro). In northwestern Europe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sciapodinae" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1022,1118,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Sciapus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laetus">
<emphasis box="[1022,1118,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">S. laetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in the coastal region where it is found most often in brackish marshlands, coastal dunes, and other 
<typeStatus box="[1104,1163,405,431]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">types</typeStatus>
of open grassy biotopes (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[159,294,441,467]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,260,539]" box="[199,646,476,503]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,476,503]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
4.6 (rare). Fairly rare (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1436,260,539]" box="[199,579,512,539]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,512,539]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Activity period.</emphasis>
July–September.
</paragraph>
